\begin{equation*}
    E^{(2)}=-\tfrac{\hbar}{\pi}\tfrac{1}{\Delta E}=-\tfrac{\hbar}{\omega\pi}.
\end{equation*}
Thus, the total second-order corrected energy is $E=\hbar\omega\bigl(1+\tfrac{1}{2}-\tfrac{1}{\pi}\bigr)$.

